
<center><section class="p-4 mb-2 bg-info text-black"><h4>Welcome to JobHouse</h4></section></center>
<div class="accordion" id="accordionExample">
  <div class="accordion-item">
    <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingOne">
      <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">
        What Is JobHouse, And Who Is It For?
      </button>
    </h2>
    <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
      <div class="accordion-body">
      <center>
      <p><em>Nearly 9 million people have moved somewhere new since the start of 2020. We built this app to help people moving somewhere new find a job, and housing that is within their means.</em></p>
        JobHouse helps users easily visualize the relationship between an employment opportunity and buying their own home. It has been and continues to be designed with <strong> YOU</strong> in mind.
      </center>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="accordion-item">
    <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingTwo">
      <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
        Find & Save A Job First
      </button>
    </h2>
    <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
      <div class="accordion-body">
        <ul>
          <li>Click Button/Link ⤦ (You Can Also Find This Button On Your Dashboard)<%= button_to 'Search For Jobs', search_jobs_path, method: :get, class: 'btn btn-info' %></li>
          <li>Fill Out Search Fields, Click <strong>Search</strong> Button.</li>
          <li>On the <strong>See Details</strong> Page, You'll Find A Button To <strong>Save</strong> The Job to Your Dashboard, As Well As An <strong>Apply</strong> Button That Links To The Live Adzuna Job Posting. </li>
          <li>Once You've Saved A Job, It Will Be Added To Your Dashboard, Where You Can <strong>Find Homes</strong> For That Specific Job</li>
          <li>You'll Then See A List Of Compatible Homes In The Same Area As The Job You've Saved </li>
          <li>Find Your Favorite Home And Click <strong>Save House</strong></li>
          <li>The Saved JobHouse Pairing Will Be Saved Under <strong>Saved Homes</strong> In Your Dashboard</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="accordion-item">
    <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingThree">
      <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
        Find & Save A House First
      </button>
    </h2>
    <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingThree" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
      <div class="accordion-body">
      <small>*Save Job Features Pending*</small>
        <ul>
          <li>Click Button/Link ⤦ (You Can Also Find This Button On Your Dashboard)<%= button_to 'Search For Houses', search_houses_path, method: :get, class: 'btn btn-info' %></li>
          <li>Fill Out Search Fields, Click <strong>Search</strong> Button.</li>
          <li>When You've Found The House You Like, Click <strong>Save House</strong> </li>
          <li>Once You've Saved A House, It Will Be Added To Your Dashboard, Where You Can <strong>Find Jobs</strong> For That Specific House</li>
          <li>You'll Then See A List Of Compatible Jobs In The Same Area As The House You've Saved </li>
          <section class="text-decoration-underline"><em>Pending Features</em></section>
          <li>Find Your Favorite Job And Click <strong>Save Job</strong></li>
          <li>The Saved JobHouse Pairing Will Be Saved Under <strong>Saved Jobs</strong> In Your Dashboard</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="accordion-item">
    <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingFour">
      <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFour">
        How Do You Calculate 'Compatible' Jobs And Houses?
      </button>
    </h2>
    <div id="collapseFour" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFour" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
      <div class="accordion-body">
      <center>
        JobHouse Compatibility Is Currently Based On General Reccommendations Regarding The <em>Average</em> That <em>Should</em> Be Allocated Towards A Housing Budget.
         Currently, We Assume A 30 Year, Fixed Rate Mortgage At 6% Interest, And That A User Would Be Willing To Spend 30% Of Their Single Income On The Mortgage.
        </center>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="accordion-item">
    <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingFive">
      <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFive" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFive">
        What Is My Dashboard?
      </button>
    </h2>
    <div id="collapseFive" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFive" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
      <div class="accordion-body">
        Your Dashboard Is The Where The <em>Magic</em> Happens! It's Where You'll Find: 
        <ul>
          <li>Homes You've Saved</li>
            <ul>
              <li>Find Jobs to Save To A Home</li>
              <li>View Jobs Previously Saved To A Home</li>
            </ul>
          <li>Jobs You've Saved</li>
            <ul>
              <li>Find Homes to Save To A Job</li>
              <li>View Homes Previously Saved To A Job</li>
            </ul>
          <li>Buttons To Search For New Jobs And Houses</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
